# Phase 3: Dynamic Thought Queue + Self-Routed Execution

## System Architecture Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Reflection/Failure] --> B[Insert Thoughts into Queue]
    B --> C{Select Top Thought}
    C -->|priority| D[Execute Thought]
    D --> E[Train, Eval, Reflect again]
    E --> A
    
    F[AZL Program] --> G[Parser]
    G --> H[AST Nodes]
    H --> I[Interpreter]
    
    I --> J{Statement Type}
    J -->|Think Command| K[ThoughtQueue.add_thoughts]
    J -->|Execute Command| L[ThoughtQueue.select]
    J -->|Mutate Command| M[ThoughtQueue.mutate_thought]
    
    K --> N[Priority Queue]
    L --> O[Thought Execution]
    M --> P[Thought Modification]
    
    O --> Q[Neural Training]
    Q --> R[Evaluation]
    R --> S[Reflection Engine]
    
    S --> T{Performance Check}
    T -->|Success| U[Promote Strategy]
    T -->|Failure| V[Trigger New Thoughts]
    
    V --> B
    U --> W[Goal Evolution]
```

## AZL Grammar for Phase 3

### Thought Declaration
```azl
thought "adjust_hyperparams" {
  modify(learning_rate, 0.001)
  add_dropout(0.2)
}
```

### Think Block (Add to Queue)
```azl
think {
  "train_mnist",
  "evaluate_mnist", 
  "adjust_hyperparams"
}
```

### Execute Commands
```azl
execute top_thought()
execute random_thought()
execute by_tag("training")
execute exact("train_mnist")
```

### Mutation Commands
```azl
mutate("train_mnist").add( dropout(0.2) )
mutate("eval_mnist").adjust_priority(0.9)
mutate("adjust_hyperparams").add_tag("optimization")
```

## Runtime Components

### ThoughtQueue
- **Priority Queue**: BinaryHeap<QueuedThought>
- **Thought Registry**: HashMap<String, Thought>
- **Execution History**: Vec<String>

### QueuedThought
- **label**: String
- **priority**: f32 (0.0-1.0)
- **created_at**: f64

### Priority Logic
- Training thoughts: 0.9
- Evaluation thoughts: 0.8
- Adjustment thoughts: 0.7
- Default: 0.5

## Integration Points

### With Neural System
- Thoughts can trigger model training
- Training results influence thought priority
- Failed training generates new thoughts

### With Reflection System
- Execution traces feed into reflection
- Reflection outcomes modify thought priorities
- Goal evolution based on performance

### With Goal System
- Thoughts can be goal-directed
- Goal achievement modifies thought selection
- Failed goals generate new thoughts

